  "prompt": "Which are the best Hollywood movies of 2016?",
  "response": "2016 was a strong year for Hollywood, with a diverse range of films that garnered critical acclaim and commercial success. Here are some of the best, categorized for easier browsing:\n\n**Critically Acclaimed & Award Winners:**\n\n*   **Moonlight:** A coming-of-age story about a young Black man grappling with his identity and sexuality. Won Best Picture at the Oscars.\n*   **La La Land:** A musical romantic drama about aspiring artists in Los Angeles. Won numerous awards, including Best Director for Damien Chazelle.\n*   **Manchester by the Sea:** A deeply moving drama about a grieving man who becomes the guardian of his nephew. Won Best Original Screenplay and Best Actor for Casey Affleck.\n*   **Arrival:** A thought-provoking science fiction film about a linguist tasked with communicating with aliens. Nominated for Best Picture and Best Director.\n*   **Hell or High Water:** A neo-Western crime thriller about two brothers robbing banks to save their family farm. Nominated for Best Picture.\n*   **Hacksaw Ridge:** A biographical war drama about Desmond Doss, a conscientious objector who served as a medic in World War II. Directed by Mel Gibson.\n\n**Commercially Successful & Popular:**\n\n*   **Captain America: Civil War:** A superhero action film that pits Captain America against Iron Man.\n*   **Rogue One: A Star Wars Story:** A Star Wars spin-off film about a group of rebels who set out to steal the plans for the Death Star.\n*   **Finding Dory:** A sequel to Finding Nemo, following Dory on a quest to find her parents.\n*   **Zootopia:** An animated film about a bunny cop and a fox con artist who team up to solve a mystery.\n*   **The Jungle Book:** A live-action/CGI adaptation of the classic Disney film.\n*   **Deadpool:** A superhero film with dark humor starring Ryan Reynolds.\n\n**Other Notable Films:**\n\n*   **Hidden Figures:** A biographical drama about three African-American women who played a vital role at NASA during the early years of the space race.\n*   **Love & Friendship:** A Jane Austen adaptation starring Kate Beckinsale.\n*   **Sing Street:** A coming-of-age musical comedy-drama set in 1980s Dublin.\n*   **10 Cloverfield Lane:** A suspenseful thriller that is a spiritual successor to Cloverfield.\n*   **Don't Breathe:** A horror-thriller about a group of friends who break into the house of a blind veteran.\n*   **Jackie:** A biographical drama about Jackie Kennedy in the days after JFK's assassination. Natalie Portman was nominated for Best Actress.\n\n**Considerations for \"Best\":**\n\n*   **Personal Preference:** What one person considers \"best\" depends on their taste in genre, themes, and acting styles.\n*   **Critical Acclaim vs. Popularity:** Some films are critical darlings but not widely seen, while others are box office hits but less respected by critics.\n*   **Long-Term Impact:** Some films resonate more strongly over time than others.\n\nThis list is a starting point. Depending on what you are looking for, I can offer more specific recommendations.  Do you have a particular genre or director in mind?",
